Preconditions:
The input grid must not be null.
The input grid must have at least one row and one column.
The input grid must be a rectangular grid, i.e., all rows must have the same number of columns.

Postconditions:
The method should return an integer value representing the maximum total sum that the height of the buildings can be increased by without changing the city's skyline.
The input grid should remain unchanged after the method execution.
The skyline of the city should remain the same from all cardinal directions after the method execution.